Line33.84B74: You boast of a mere fragment of what this once was. The worldstone, debased in the hands of fools.
Line11.84B74: The time of prophecy has come, Knights. Lilith flees through the gate to Hell.
Line29.6D03F: We don’t need the bloody angels either.
Line39.84B74: You who die in battle today, die Heaven-bound!
Line41.84B74: Rally the troops at the palace. We march on Hell.
Line35.84B74: Lilith dies by my blade. Prophecy has foretold it.
Line23.84B74: Ah. The Horadrim. Always chasing after the battles of your betters.
Line25.84B74: But the angels don’t need you.
Line37.84B74: I will slay her in that cesspit she calls home and open the way to the Heavens. All is as fate decreed: “A spear of Light, piercing Hatred’s heart.”
